{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/39381", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/39381/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/39381/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/39381/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/39381", "id": 203851569, "node_id": "MDU6SXNzdWUyMDM4NTE1Njk=", "number": 39381, "title": "all Error types should be public?", "user": {"login": "getreu", "id": 579082, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjU3OTA4Mg==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/579082?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/getreu", "html_url": "https://github.com/getreu", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/getreu/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/getreu/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/getreu/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/getreu/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/getreu/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/getreu/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/getreu/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/getreu/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/getreu/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [{"id": 211668062, "node_id": "MDU6TGFiZWwyMTE2NjgwNjI=", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/labels/T-libs-api", "name": "T-libs-api", "color": "bfd4f2", "default": false, "description": "Relevant to the library API team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue."}], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 6, "created_at": "2017-01-29T05:21:38Z", "updated_at": "2017-05-25T23:14:06Z", "closed_at": "2017-05-23T20:38:40Z", "author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "In order to test the error behaviour of a function you need an error struct to compare with. For example:\r\nsince `ParseIntError` is private, I have to generate one by doing something wrong, like `u8::from_str(\"257\")`. This leads to the following test:\r\n\r\n```\r\nlet pie_overflow      = u8::from_str(\"257\").unwrap_err();\r\nassert_eq!(super::Missions::parse_enc_opt(\"ascii,256,U+41..U+67\",8).unwrap_err(), pie_overflow );\r\n```\r\n\r\nIf error types where public I would rather instantiate one and write:\r\n\r\n```\r\nlet pie_overflow  = ParseIntError {kind: std::num::Overflow};\r\nassert_eq!(super::Missions::parse_enc_opt(\"ascii,256,U+41..U+67\",8).unwrap_err(), pie_overflow );\r\n```\r\n\r\nMaybe there is a reason I do not see why they are private and there is better more idiomatic way of doing error comparison? ", "closed_by": {"login": "aturon", "id": 709807, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjcwOTgwNw==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/709807?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/aturon", "html_url": "https://github.com/aturon", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/aturon/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/aturon/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/aturon/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/aturon/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/aturon/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/aturon/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/aturon/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/aturon/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/aturon/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/39381/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confu